  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving health services for children and adolescents who live with HIV &amp; AIDS</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Thailand, many ethnic minority communities &#x2013; including hill tribes and migrants from neighbouring countries &#x2013; lack access to life saving HIV information and services, such as the timely testing and treating of children, and the prevention of HIV transmission from mother to child. Also, increasing numbers of HIV positive children in Thailand are reaching adolescence and facing extremely challenging issues. By supporting this project, it aims to help ethnic minority communities to better protect their children from HIV, and help HIV positive teenagers to cope with the challenges of living with HIV.</narrative>
  </description>
